rComments: Unclear on assignment, unclear on grading, no feedback, rude to minority student, unfair, unhelpful, hard to understand her English. Do not take her classes.

Very kind prof; really takes into consideration students' needs. Like when we complained to her about not giving the class many opportunities to 'participate,' the very next class she fixed it. She is monotone, but don't forget at the end of the day, you paid to be here. I highly suggest reading the textbook and taking notes well before exam time.
I like her, her exams are fair and she takes into consideration suggestions from students
Ok, first of can we have a teacher that speak english her korean accent is killing me.  Big nono don't take with her.... she is dumb.

She's a horrible teacher. If you can't explain things and is terribly boring, find another profession that suits you. OMG!i dont understan the scanning process these profs have to go threw to get a job. its almost like they pick names out of a hat. If you want to change your major from marketing to something else this is the class that will do it for you.

AVOID TAKING HER CLASS! Her English is very hard to understand with her heavy accent, very inflexible with changing things around, asks us to have name tags displayed and she TAKES ATTENDANCE!  @_@ Too bad she's the only B04 prof for this term, we have no choice...
